The government intends to have the Daadab and Kakuma refugee camps closed down by July next year. Kenya states that this closure will be preceded by either repatriation of refugees or issuance of work permits that will enable them to contribute to the country&rsquo;s &ldquo;social-economic growth&rdquo;. but as KTN's Ibrahim Karanja reports, whether or not this plan will be implemented remains to be seen, as this is not the first time the country is making such threats.